         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head><p><supplied reason="subaudible">In honour</supplied> of Elpidius. To a man deserving praise for all virtues, distinguished and magnificent for goodness beyond documentation, Caecilius Severus, splendid man<note> of senatorial status</note>, acting as deputy for the praetorian prefects; the Lepcitanians <supplied reason="subaudible">set this up</supplied> publicly on account of the manifold moderation of his judgments in their cases, and in accordance with a decree and a vote <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character" precision="low"/>  </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>l. 1. Elpidius. Perhaps to be identified with <title level="m">PW</title> VIII, 206, 1 and if so <foreign xml:lang="la">vicarius</foreign> in 321. See also <title>ILS</title> 8730. </p>
